title: For Sale:  Limited Edition Spikes Tactical Upper w Nickel Boron BCG
postcontent:
Brand new complete Spikes Tactical upper assembly that will drop right onto any AR15 lower in 5.45X39 (which is arguably a better round than .223, with the same ballistics and it is MUCH cheaper). Same caliber as the AK74 and 1080 round sealed cans of Russian surplus are still only about $180, so about $.16 per round. This caliber is by far the cheapest military spec'ed ammo available on the planet, and at that price you can afford to buy several cans and stack them deep, they come sealed airtight and will last forever. Upper is factory built from Spikes with a top quality $375 Lothar Walther barrel. Also, the entire upper has the ultimate in corrosion resistant finishes. It is Melonite treated inside and out including even the flash hider and front sight / gas block, and comes complete with a new complete $275 Spikes Tactical NiB (Nickel Boron) treated all milspec BCG. As a bonus, the carrier is exactly the same as a 5.56 carrier, so you can also use this Nickel Boron carrier in your regular .223/5.56 AR15 upper just by swapping your standard 5.56 bolt into it. It will save you a fortune in ammo and 5.45x39 is an awesome round. This upper was a limited production run that was designed and built specifically to chew through cheap surplus ammo, and it is a steal for the price when you consider the complete anti-corrosion finish package, a $375 high end LW barrel, a $275 Spikes NiB BCG, and the HUGE savings in the price of ammo. 1080 rounds of 5.45 is over $400 CHEAPER than 1000 rounds of .223 or 5.56, so by the time you buy 2 of the 1080 round cans of ammo you have saved more than the entire price of the complete upper basically making it free. It is well worth the extra $100-$200 for this upper just for the Nickel Boron BCG alone. It is brand new still in the box and comes complete with Spikes Tactical's Lifetime Warranty.

title: For Sale:  8 Day MD Handgun Transfer
postcontent:
Many pistols, both Rev. & Semi available from $100.
My understanding of MD law is that there are two ways to legally transfer regulated firearms , thru a dealer or thru Md State Police.  Everyone is bemoaning how low MSP
background checks are taking.  60 + days is common.  
- Dealers will not release a purchased item until they receive a clear background check from MSP.  
- As two individuals, you apply at MSP for $10, wait the statute required 7 days, and can then pass the purchased firearm.  If the background comes back flawed, It's on 
the MSP to retrieve it.
Anyone having a different understanding is welcome to contact me.
